{
  "texts": [
    "Yao et al. (2018) divide the interests into two groups according to the probability of interest appearing and the average time interval between two interests requesting the same content.",
    "Each router then broadcasts a list of suspect content items to its neighbors in order to prevent them from being cached.",
    "This helps in the final phase of determining if the attack is a Locality Disruption Attack (LDA) or False Locality Attack (FLA).",
    "In their research, Gupta and Nahar (2021) constructed a method that may detect CPA by including the K-Means Clustering algorithm.",
    "The authors make use of the information that is associated with each interest, and then they sort it into either the LDA or FLA category."
  ]
}